    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sepulchral monuments in the form of freestanding pillars; distinguished by being taller and generally having less breadth than a tombstone or a stele, but often having more depth. Grave pillars were common in several ancient cultures and continue in modern usage. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
